cited three gatherings in the protologue: 
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81CFFD2FBE08E6166E1F9AB" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Bourgeau 2536, Bourgeau 1753, Ross 1158</emphasis>
, and he cited the herbaria housing the specimens that he examined (
<collectionCode id="ED7CAE4DA81CFFD2FC5C8E0C65B8F9AB" box="[958,999,1608,1634]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">BR</collectionCode>
, G, MPU, P, and S). We located most of the original material that he cited and annotated: 
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81CFFD2FD428E296515F94F" box="[672,842,1644,1670]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Bourgeau 2536</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED7CAE4DA81CFFD2FCB58E286521F94F" box="[855,894,1644,1670]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">BR</collectionCode>
barcode 000000552905]), G barcode G00415142, MPU barcode MPU310734, P barcode P00385091, P barcode P00385092, S [not seen]); 
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81CFFD2FB888ED56349F963" box="[1130,1302,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Bourgeau 1753</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED7CAE4DA81CFFD2FAC78ED46313F963" box="[1317,1356,1680,1706]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">BR</collectionCode>
barcode 000000552839, G barcode G00415141, M barcode M-0171795, MPU barcode MPU310733, P barcode P00368664, P barcode P00368663, S [not seen]; 
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81CFFD2FDC98E9D64C0F93B" box="[555,671,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Ross 1158</emphasis>
(M barcode M-0171796). The 
<emphasis id="B919EA9AA81CFFD2FBE58E9D62EAF93B" box="[1031,1205,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Bourgeau 2536</emphasis>
specimen at 
<collectionCode id="ED7CAE4DA81CFFD2FAAC8E9D632CF93A" box="[1358,1395,1753,1779]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">BR</collectionCode>
(
<collectionCode id="ED7CAE4DA81CFFD2FA668E9C63F4F93B" box="[1412,1451,1752,1778]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">BR</collectionCode>
barcode 000000552905) is selected here as the 
<typeStatus id="54D6882AA81CFFD2FD788EB8655EF8DF" box="[666,769,1788,1814]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">lectotype</typeStatus>
for the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D0BA81CFFD2FC7E8EB86222F8DF" authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" box="[924,1149,1788,1814]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anomala">
